unittitle_ssm: New York University Surveys
abstract_ssm: The reports in this collection span a forty-one year period, from 1932-1973, although the majority of the data is from 1930-1962. The surveys were commissioned and conducted by University administration, consultants commissioned by the University Council, and the Chancellor's Office. The survey material contains a range of data about the history of New York University, the history of higher education, the role of NYU as an urban university, and the relationship of the university with its city and region.
